<br>
The staff is a joke. 2hb, decent ratio, but no wizard will use that ratio. +8 INT on an item which takes up 2 slots = very, very bad idea. You can have a Stien of moggok at like level 12, which I would use over this any day, and still have a free hand for another INT item or a weapon. <br>
When will Verant understand that we get much better stats wielding two items rather than their sub-par 2hb items? And it doesn't even have an effect! I was hoping that this would be the upgrade to the Staff of Flux that we've asked for since the Sol Ro quests were finished, and guess what? It sucks.<br>
<br>
The sandels are less than average. Sure, it's slightly difficult to find a foot slot item with INT on it around the level you'd be doing these quests, but the stats aren't that impressive at all.<br>
<br>
The gloves are very sub-par. There are so many better gloves out there available at 10 levels less than required to do these quests, it's disgusting. Imp Skin gloves drop in Sol A, and you can get them at level 30ish with a small group. Dusty Bloodstained gloves are going for 25pp on my server, and I'd wear those over the gloves of detonation.<br>
<br>
So, if Verant thinks these items are better than the solusek Ro items, they're insane. There are more of them, sure, but the overall stats are quite low compared to what you can loot at these levels. Once again, nice job at showing us what Everquest means; Quest for what seems like forever, and you'll recieve an item which is worth less than what you can buy or loot from a MoB that you kill in a few hours.<br>
<br>
